Gradient of the scalar field

using Plots
using ForwardDiff

f(x, y) = 200 - x^2 - 2*y^2

∂f_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> f(x_, y), x)
∂f_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> f(x, y_), y)

F(x, y) = (∂f_∂x(x, y), ∂f_∂y(x, y))

xvals = -1:1:1
yvals = -1:1:1

X = repeat(xvals, inner=length(yvals))
Y = repeat(yvals, outer=length(xvals))
U = [F(xi, yi)[1] for (xi, yi) in zip(X, Y)] #zip ensures a 1-to-1 mapping 
V = [F(xi, yi)[2] for (xi, yi) in zip(X, Y)]#between X and Y for your quiver plot.

quiver(X, Y, quiver=(U, V), xlabel="x", ylabel="y", 
       title="Gradient Vector Field  of f(x,y) = 200 - x^2 - 2y^2")

In [150]:
using ForwardDiff

function Divergence(x,y) #defining divergence 
    f(x,y) = x
    g(x,y) = -(y^2)

    ∂f_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> f(x_, y), x)
    ∂g_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> g(x, y_), y)
    
    C = ∂f_∂x(x, y) + ∂g_∂y(x, y)
    return C
end

p = -2:0.1:2
q = -2:0.1:2

Z = [Divergence(xi, yi) for yi in q, xi in p]


plot(p, q, Z; xlabel="x", ylabel="y",
    title="Divergence of f(x,y) = xe₁ - y²e₂", colorbar_title="divergence")

using ForwardDiff

function Curl(x,y)
    f(x,y) = x
    g(x,y) = -(y^2)

    ∂f_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> f(x, y_), y)
    ∂g_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> g(x_, y), x)

    C = ∂g_∂x(x, y) - ∂f_∂y(x, y)
    return C
end

p = -2:0.1:2
q = -2:0.1:2

Z = [Curl(xi, yi) for yi in q, xi in p]

surface(p, q, Z; xlabel="x", ylabel="y", 
        title="Curl of f(x,y) = xe₁ - y²e₂",colorbar_title="curl")

using ForwardDiff

function Divergence(x,y)
    f(x,y) = exp(x) * y^2
    g(x,y) = x + 2*y

    ∂f_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> f(x_, y), x)
    ∂g_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> g(x, y_), y)
    C = ∂f_∂x(x, y) + ∂g_∂y(x, y)
    return C
end

p = -2:0.1:2
q = -2:0.1:2

Z = [Divergence(xi, yi) for yi in q, xi in p]

plot(p, q, Z;  xlabel="x", ylabel="y", 
title="Divergence of f(x,y) = (eˣy²)e₁ + (x+2y)e₂",colorbar_title="divergence")

using CalculusWithJulia, Plots

f(u) = [exp(u[1]) * u[2]^2, u[1] + 2u[2]]

c = curl(f)

x = -2:0.5:2
y = -2:0.5:2

X = repeat(x, inner=length(y))
Y = repeat(y, outer=length(x))

Zf(x,y) = c([x,y])
Z= [Zf(xi, yi) for (xi, yi) in zip(X,Y)]

∂Z_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> Zf(x_, y), x)
∂Z_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> Zf(x, y_), y)

normal = [[∂Z_∂x(xi, yi), ∂Z_∂y(xi, yi), 0.0] for (xi, yi) in zip(X,Y) ]

U = [n[1] for n in normal]
V = [n[2] for n in normal]
W = [n[3] for n in normal]

L = [sqrt(u^2+v^2+w^2) for (u,v,w) in zip(U,V,W)]
U = U ./ L
V = V ./ L
W = W ./ L

surface(X, Y, Z; xlabel="x", ylabel="y",
    title="Curl of f(x,y) = (eˣy²)e₁ + (x+2y)e₂",  colorbar_title="curl")
quiver!(X,Y,Z, quiver=(U,V,W),color=:red)

using ForwardDiff

function Curl(x,y)
    f(x,y) = exp(x) * y^2
    g(x,y) = x + 2*y

    ∂f_∂y(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(y_ -> f(x, y_), y)
    ∂g_∂x(x, y) = ForwardDiff.derivative(x_ -> g(x_, y), x)

    C = ∂g_∂x(x, y) - ∂f_∂y(x, y)
    return C
end

p = -2:0.2:2
q = -2:0.2:2

Z = [Curl(xi, yi) for yi in q, xi in p]



surface(p, q, Z; xlabel="x", ylabel="y", 
    title="Curl of f(x,y) = (eˣy²)e₁ + (x+2y)e₂",  colorbar_title="curl")
quiver!(p, q, Z)

using Plots
q = 2
l = 10
L = 1.25*l
Ay = 0.375*q*L
By = 0.625*q*L

function SfdBmd(q,l,L,Ay,By)
    x = 0:0.1:L
    Sf = zeros(length(x))
    for (i, xi) in enumerate(x)
        if xi<l || xi==l
            Sf[i] = Ay - (q*xi)
        else
            Sf[i] = Ay + By - (q*xi)
        end
    end

    Bm = zeros(length(x))
    for (i, xi) in enumerate(x)
        if xi<l || xi==l
            Bm[i] = (Ay*xi) - (q*xi*xi*0.5)
        else
            Bm[i] = (Ay*xi) + By*(xi-l) - (q*xi*xi*0.5)
        end
    end
        
    p1 = plot(x,Sf, xlabel = "distance from hinge (m)", ylabel = "Shear Force (N)",
              title = "SFD", legend = false, color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([0,0], [0,Sf[1]],color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([L,L], [0,Sf[length(x)]],color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([0,L], [0,0])

    p2 = plot(x,Bm, xlabel = "distance from hinge (m)", ylabel = "Bending Moment (Nm)", 
              title = "BMD", legend = false, color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([0,0], [0,Bm[1]],color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([L,L], [0,Bm[length(x)]],color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([0,L], [0,0])

    plot(p1,p2 ; layout = (2,1))
end

SfdBmd(q,l,L,Ay,By)

using Plots
q = 2
l = 10
L = 2*l
Ay = 0.4*q*l
By = 0.98*q*l
Cy = 0.42*q*l

function SfdBmd(q,l,L,Ay,By)
    x = 0:0.01:L
    Sf = zeros(length(x))
    for (i, xi) in enumerate(x)
        if xi<=0.4l
            Sf[i] = Ay
        elseif xi>0.4l && xi<=l
            Sf[i] = Ay - 0.8*q*l
        else
            Sf[i] = Ay + By - 0.8*q*l - q*(xi-l)
        end
    end

    Bm = zeros(length(x))
    for (i, xi) in enumerate(x)
        if xi<=0.4l
            Bm[i] = (Ay*xi)
        elseif xi>0.4l && xi<=l
            Bm[i] = (Ay*xi) - (0.8*q*l*(xi-0.4*l))
        else
            Bm[i] = (Ay*xi)+(By*(xi-l))-(0.8*q*l*(xi-0.4*l))-(q*(xi-l)*(xi-l)*0.5)
        end
    end
        
    p1 = plot(x,Sf, xlabel = "distance from hinge (m)", ylabel = "Shear Force (N)",
              title = "SFD", legend = false, color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([0,0], [0,Sf[1]],color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([L,L], [0,Sf[length(x)]],color=:green)
    p1 = plot!([0,L], [0,0])

    p2 = plot(x,Bm, xlabel = "distance from hinge (m)", ylabel = "Bending Moment (N)",
              title = "BMD", legend = false, color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([0,0], [0,Bm[1]],color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([L,L], [0,Bm[length(x)]],color=:green)
    p2 = plot!([0,L], [0,0])

    plot(p1,p2 ; layout = (2,1))
  
end

SfdBmd(q,l,L,Ay,By)
